# Business-in-a-Box package (server-side)
#
# These values come from Site Builder → Developer → Package API & Unkey keys.
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (never commit it). On Vercel, set the same
# three values as Environment Variables on the Production / Preview scopes.
#
# When you want to run the demo against a locally running host, point the base
# URL at http://localhost:3000/api/package/v1 and leave the production values
# in the Vercel dashboard only.

# Keys must include tenant_auth:public for `/api/biab-auth/sign-in` (included
# in Site Builder → Developer defaults; optional override for platform-issued keys).
BIAB_API_KEY=biab_YourKeyFromSiteBuilderDevPanel
BIAB_SITE_ID=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
BIAB_PACKAGE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-host.example.com/api/package/v1

# Optional: tenant auth (`/api/biab-auth`, header “Log in”) — redirect URI must match WorkOS
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://localhost:3000
# BIAB_AUTH_CALLBACK_URL=https://your-tenant-site.com/api/biab-auth/callback
# Dev: if those are unset, callback URL is derived from the request (e.g. http://localhost:3001/...).
# Register that exact URL in WorkOS when the dev port is not 3000.

# Optional: if your generated client reads a public base URL
# NEXT_PUBLIC_BIAB_PACKAGE_API_BASE_URL=

# Customer portal server demo (`/customer`): uses BIAB_PACKAGE_API_BASE_URL + BIAB_API_KEY.
# Pin a WorkOS org when the key can access more than one; otherwise omit.
# BIAB_CUSTOMER_PORTAL_ORG_ID=org_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# Browser proxy demo (`/customer-browser`): same-origin proxy at /api/biab/customer-portal.
